The following documentation suggests that it&#x27;s possible to fetch public SSH keys using OAuth (see the "Account" section):\\
https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/meta/authentication

This does not reflect the truth, however - When attempting to fetch the SSH keys using OAuth, the following response is thrown:

{code}
#!bash
{"type": "error", "error": {"message": "This API is only accessible with the following authentication types: session, password, apppassword"}}

{code}

When I try to promote a deployment, the deployment preview dialog is show. Then I click the deploy button and the modal hangs indefinitely with the spinner showing.

In dev tools I see:

{code:Uncaught}
    at setTimeout (DeploymentPreviewDialog.2d0ce.js:3)
    at o (vendor.79291.js:1)
{code}
